column5: Looks great Dann!!  Will be sure to stop in for a cup of java if I'm in the area. I'd keep Geoff out of the hut as well.
Hey now, LOL!
looks great dan congrats
Only thing missing is a DJ and a mirror ball. Other than that, looks very cozy.
i think with that material you will be warm enough even without a heater
Awesome job, AND in the summer you can use it for a ... umm ahem... grow house!!
Sheesh Skeets You got some reputation dude !!!
HEMP HUT now taking orders free shipping for orders over 1LB
i'm telling mom on you.
looking good Skeeter almost as nice as Don's lol.ok maybe better
Nice looking set up. Good idea with the folding beds.
Thanks for the replies everyone. it does give me a little more pride when it was done with my son helping.   i'm telling mom on you!!!!!  Bully
YA WELL............MOM ALWAYS LOVE YOU MORE YA BROWN NOSER

well I'm happy to report that the remodelling is finally done. my son (Daniel) and I put a lot of work into it. its going to be nice and warm now.  the shelf for the helmets and sleeping bags   the fold up kitchen counter with 2 shelves above it for plates, spices,coffee,sugar,ect.....   with the table and beds folded up   now with the beds and table down   the outside so ALL the members can recognize it when they stop by to say hello & shoot the crap, have a coffee.     the new addition will have to wait until summer to get its paint job. if you can think of some thing i missed putting in the hut let me know. keeping in mind its only 6'x8'
Nice looking hut.    Just finished mine this fall. I'll have to take a few pictures to post
that looks warm   and shiny
VERRRRY nice Skeeter!!   Now, some GPS coordinates would be great!!! LOL
grow op or ice fishin going down in there? lol  only thing it's maybe missing is a more secure lock to keep the hooligans on simcoe out of it  nicely done, sharp looking!
Yo Skeets !!! all yer missin is a flat screen TV and a recliner.Cripes i could live in a castle like that man ! ya done good Dann.
How many holes in the floor? Can you keep a line in all night? We have holes in the corners and have lines fixed right to the wall. We fish all night, the bells wake us up.

Terry there is 1 1/2"styrofoam insulation in the floor,walls & ceiling. then the Reflectix which has a Class A/Class 1 Fire Rating .  Cliff you know you have an open invitation any time.  Bare foot, i NEVER lock the hut, if you do the idiots will kick the door in to see what they can steal. and i never leave anything in the hut for them, not even garbage.
very kewl.  What about lights that are battery operated ?
1 hole 59"x21" but i use the auger so i can cut up to 6 holes.

thanks splashhopper, i forgot to mention that part. i bought an rv light from princess auto today $6.99 (2 bulb unit) and installed a 12v fan on the ceiling to blow the heat back down (5" computer fan).

And if u really wanna stay warm, when u sleep there overnight, grab those plug in seat heaters for cars... put it under your sleeping bag and hook it up to the battery.... toasty warm and doesn't take up any room... and can be used double duty over those wooded seats while fishing
flat screen tv--lol well i do have a 5" portable that runs on 12volt recliner--no way , i want to be awake if i get a fish on...
The hut looks great Dann!  I'll be in the area you put it out either the end of Jan. or Feb.    Cliff, we can go fish beside his hut as we all know he's a great lure washer...
looks cozy!!!
BEDS?!  AWESOME....when can i move in?   Nice shack Skeets.
Cliff, we can go fish beside his hut as we all know he's a great lure washer  but you will be cold and Cliff will be warm and drinking a hot coffee....
you might want to wait till its out on the ice, could be a bumpy ride going out.LOL but it is only .6km away from the lake in lefroy!!!
Looks really cozy, nice job
Awesome work Skeet I noticed you don't have place for a wood stove.... what do you use for heating???  Leechman
the "aroma" from Mrs Kelly's AMAZING Chili...
Nope, the clam 2000 and the heater can tag along for a visit too.
chili--LOL it would work but the carbon monoxide detector wouldnt shut up...  i use a propane camp stove, heats the hut and heats up the food , and of course my coffee too.
Nice shelter...you finished it right on time too.
